==English==

===Pronunciation===
*chēk, /tʃiːk/, /<tt>tSi:k</tt>/
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[cēace]]''
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# {{anatomy}} The soft skin on each side of the face, below the eyes; the outer surface of the sides of the oral cavity.<!--prefer "oral cavity" to "mouth" for clarity; "mouth" could mean "lips" - Paul G, 1 February 2005-->
# (''colloquial''; ''usually in plural'') A [[buttock]].
# (''colloquial'') [[Impudence]].
#:''You’ve got some '''cheek''', asking me for money!''

====Synonyms====
*(''impudence''):
**(''standard''): [[impertinence]], [[impudence]]
**(''colloquial/slang''): [[brass neck]], [[nerve]], [[sass]] (''especially US'')

